I left them in charge of the ship in mid-attack, and this is how they repay me.

271
00:13:02,680 --> 00:13:04,760
I'm unhappy. Hina unhappy.

272
00:13:05,460 --> 00:13:06,970
Have all ships been deployed?

273
00:13:07,020 --> 00:13:08,780
Yes, Ma'am! All of them!

274
00:13:08,780 --> 00:13:11,790
All the docks in Arabasta have been blockaded by our 30-ship fleet with reinforcements!

275
00:13:12,330 --> 00:13:13,250
But...

276
00:13:14,360 --> 00:13:16,360
There is one thing that worries me.

277
00:13:16,360 --> 00:13:17,090
What?

278
00:13:17,190 --> 00:13:22,780
The vessel belonging to the Straw Hat Pirates that was sighted at Erumalu is gone.

279
00:13:22,780 --> 00:13:24,640
You're telling me they've already fled the country?

280
00:13:24,640 --> 00:13:26,380
No, that couldn't have happened, but-

281
00:13:26,380 --> 00:13:27,790
Then find it!

282
00:13:27,790 --> 00:13:28,930
Search coast to coast!

283
00:13:28,930 --> 00:13:30,100
Yes Ma'am! At once!

284
00:13:30,500 --> 00:13:31,450
Honestly...

285
00:13:31,450 --> 00:13:32,470
Hina-jou!

286
00:13:32,470 --> 00:13:34,160
We are late!

287
00:13:34,160 --> 00:13:36,310
Please ask us why we are late.

288
00:13:36,310 --> 00:13:37,750
Why are you late?

289
00:13:37,750 --> 00:13:40,130
We picked flowers, just for you~!

290
00:13:40,130 --> 00:13:41,080
I don't want them.

291
00:13:41,310 --> 00:13:42,930
Return to your positions!

292
00:13:43,030 --> 00:13:44,890
We're going after the Straw Hat Pirates!

293
00:13:44,890 --> 00:13:46,490
S-STRAW HAT!?

294
00:13:51,010 --> 00:13:52,010
I like this!

295
00:13:52,010 --> 00:13:54,590
Farewell, oh country of sand!

296
00:13:54,590 --> 00:13:56,430
Oi, Luffy, you still eating?

297
00:13:56,430 --> 00:13:58,470
Arabasta food is the best!

298
00:13:58,470 --> 00:14:00,050
Sanji, make some of this tomorrow!

299
00:14:00,050 --> 00:14:02,050
Sure, I was interested in it too.

300
00:14:02,050 --> 00:14:04,040
I got some recipes off Terracotta-san.

301
00:14:04,040 --> 00:14:05,330
And I picked up some spices too.

302
00:14:06,260 --> 00:14:08,630
Nami, are you feeling sick?

303
00:14:10,560 --> 00:14:12,520
Nami, want a piece of meat?

304
00:14:12,520 --> 00:14:13,440
But only one.

305
00:14:15,380 --> 00:14:17,800
Nami-san, it's about Vivi-chan, isn't it?

306
00:14:17,800 --> 00:14:19,430
I understand how you feel...

307
00:14:19,430 --> 00:14:22,550
But if you keep thinking so much, you'll never get over it.

308
00:14:23,070 --> 00:14:25,630
You two were good friends for so long...

309
00:14:25,630 --> 00:14:28,110
But c'mon, look up.

310
00:14:33,030 --> 00:14:34,310
I'm...

311
00:14:38,020 --> 00:14:39,420
...giving it up.

312
00:14:39,740 --> 00:14:41,030
For Vivi.

313
00:14:41,920 --> 00:14:43,220
My 1,000,000,000 beri

314
00:14:43,430 --> 00:14:44,520
OF COURSE YOU ARE!!

315
00:14:44,520 --> 00:14:45,960
YOU WERE TALKING ABOUT MONEY!!?

316
00:14:46,440 --> 00:14:47,820
USOPP FELL OFF!

317
00:14:47,820 --> 00:14:50,120
NAMI! Quit being so damn misleading!

318
00:14:50,120 --> 00:14:52,070
Huh? What's your problem?

319
00:14:52,070 --> 00:14:54,620
There's no point worrying about Vivi!

320
00:14:54,620 --> 00:14:56,370
Oi! Usopp has FALLEN OFF!

321
00:14:56,370 --> 00:14:57,790
That's his problem!

322
00:14:57,790 --> 00:14:59,460
IT'S YOUR FAULT!

323
00:15:00,520 --> 00:15:01,270
Carue!

324
00:15:01,470 --> 00:15:02,810
Is Carue here!?

325
00:15:04,450 --> 00:15:05,870
It won't work, Igaram.

326
00:15:05,870 --> 00:15:06,970
Why?

327
00:15:06,970 --> 00:15:09,460
They should at least know where they now stand in society!

328
00:15:09,460 --> 00:15:11,280
I sent them on the Super Spot-billed Duck Squad.

329
00:15:11,280 --> 00:15:13,010
Even Carue wouldn't be able to catch up now.

330
00:15:13,250 --> 00:15:14,930
And it would only be the same.

331
00:15:14,930 --> 00:15:15,930
What would?

332
00:15:16,110 --> 00:15:18,970
Knowing that would just make them happier.

333
00:15:18,970 --> 00:15:20,210
Nothing would change.

334
00:15:20,460 --> 00:15:21,260
But-

335
00:15:21,260 --> 00:15:22,990
You don't have to worry about them!

336
00:15:22,990 --> 00:15:24,640
Now get out!

337
00:15:24,640 --> 00:15:25,800
I'm going to sleep.

338
00:15:25,800 --> 00:15:27,090
Early start tomorrow, right?

339
00:15:27,090 --> 00:15:28,600
Oh yes, indeed!

340
00:15:28,800 --> 00:15:31,780
Tomorrow you must deliver a speech to the country.

341
00:15:31,780 --> 00:15:33,170
I know.

342
00:15:33,380 --> 00:15:35,600
Come on, Carue. Let's sleep together.

343
00:15:42,910 --> 00:15:43,850
Igaram-san...

344
00:15:43,850 --> 00:15:45,240
Something is not right...

345
00:15:45,240 --> 00:15:46,210
What do you mean?

346
00:15:47,090 --> 00:15:48,790
She was too blithe about it...

347
00:15:50,650 --> 00:15:51,640
Something is wrong...

348
00:15:51,910 --> 00:15:53,400
Something is very wrong...

349
00:16:01,550 --> 00:16:03,850
It's so quiet... Carue.

350
00:16:05,260 --> 00:16:07,780
It's been so long since we've had a night this quiet.

351
00:16:08,470 --> 00:16:12,260
No more refrigerator burglar and the fighting cook...

352
00:16:12,680 --> 00:16:15,650
Or the swordsman doing his night training...

353
00:16:15,870 --> 00:16:18,710
Or the half-awake, pillow-throwing navigator...

354
00:16:20,060 --> 00:16:21,800
They're all gone.

355
00:16:25,650 --> 00:16:28,000
A Den Den Mushi? From who?

356
00:16:28,340 --> 00:16:29,930
From someone named "Bon-chan".

357
00:16:29,930 --> 00:16:31,380
Bon-chan? Who's that?

358
00:16:31,380 --> 00:16:32,970
We don't know him.

359
00:16:32,970 --> 00:16:35,990
But he claims to be your friend, so...

360
00:16:35,990 --> 00:16:37,180
Friend?

361
00:16:38,420 --> 00:16:39,680
Hello, hello?

362
00:16:39,800 --> 00:16:41,370
Hel-lo~!?

363
00:16:42,440 --> 00:16:43,370
It's ME!

364
00:16:43,370 --> 00:16:44,970
It. Is. ME!

365
00:16:47,520 --> 00:16:49,120
WHAT IS IT!?

366
00:16:50,540 --> 00:16:51,540
Oh, it's you.

367
00:16:51,540 --> 00:16:53,040
What do you want with us?

368
00:16:53,040 --> 00:16:53,890
Oh!?

369
00:16:53,890 --> 00:16:56,430
Isn't that the voice of Straw-chan!?

370
00:16:56,430 --> 00:16:59,630
You're so strooong~! I was so surprised~!

371
00:16:59,630 --> 00:17:02,760
Oh, yes, yes! Don't go calling me Mr. 2!

372
00:17:02,760 --> 00:17:05,810
If the Marines get wind of this conversation, I'll be in super big trouble!

373
00:17:05,810 --> 00:17:07,640
He just said it himself!

374
00:17:07,640 --> 00:17:08,980
Just spit it out.

375
00:17:09,080 --> 00:17:10,290
Ah, right, right, right.

376
00:17:10,290 --> 00:17:12,650
I took your little ship!

377
00:17:12,650 --> 00:17:13,870
WHAT THE HELL!?

378
00:17:13,870 --> 00:17:16,610
Asshole! That ain't funny! Where are you now!?

379
00:17:16,610 --> 00:17:18,670
I'm on your boooaaat~!

380
00:17:18,670 --> 00:17:20,080
Of all the annoying bastards in the world...

381
00:17:20,080 --> 00:17:23,710
You've got it wrooong, all wrooong~!

382
00:17:23,910 --> 00:17:27,910
Aren't you and I friends~?

383
00:17:33,710 --> 00:17:36,310
He's upstream on the Sandora River.

384
00:17:36,600 --> 00:17:38,220
Can we trust him?

385
00:17:38,220 --> 00:17:40,610
We were friends with him before...

386
00:17:40,610 --> 00:17:42,910
The idea of you becoming friends again scares me.

387
00:17:42,910 --> 00:17:44,810
But... we don't really have a choice.

388
00:17:44,810 --> 00:17:46,860
That's right. He's got our ship.

389
00:17:46,860 --> 00:17:50,330
If he's trying anything funny, we'll just kick his ass.

390
00:17:50,450 --> 00:17:52,110
Then let's get moving already.

391
00:17:52,110 --> 00:17:53,690
Yosh, let's get going.

392
00:17:53,690 --> 00:17:55,110
If the ship is taken, we gotta...

393
00:17:55,110 --> 00:17:56,520
Hey, everyone...

394
00:18:00,240 --> 00:18:02,370
Hey... everyone...

395
00:18:04,250 --> 00:18:08,690
What should I do?

396
00:18:10,690 --> 00:18:11,900
Listen carefully, Vivi.

397
00:18:11,900 --> 00:18:14,220
We'll give you twelve hours to think.

398
00:18:13,670 --> 00:18:23,560
Sandora River

399
00:18:13,670 --> 00:18:23,560
Nanohana

400
00:18:13,670 --> 00:18:23,560
Current Location


401
00:18:18,760 --> 00:18:23,560
Eastern Harbor

402
00:18:14,220 --> 00:18:17,350
After we take back our ship on the Sandora River,

403
00:18:17,350 --> 00:18:19,260
Then exactly at noon tomorrow,

404
00:18:19,360 --> 00:18:22,080
We'll swing the ship past the eastern harbor once.

405
00:18:22,080 --> 00:18:24,210
I doubt we'll be able to drop anchor,

406
00:18:24,210 --> 00:18:27,220
So if you want to keep adventuring with us,

407
00:18:27,220 --> 00:18:29,700
That will be the last chance you'll have to jump on board.

408
00:18:30,480 --> 00:18:34,550
If so, we'll celebrate! As pirates!

409
00:18:34,630 --> 00:18:38,780
You're the Princess of the Kingdom, so this is the best invitation we can give you.

410
00:18:38,780 --> 00:18:39,990
Come, Vivi!

411
00:18:39,990 --> 00:18:41,360
You have to come! Come right now!

412
00:18:41,360 --> 00:18:42,450
Stop it, Luffy!

413
00:18:42,450 --> 00:18:43,400
Let's go!

414
00:18:43,400 --> 00:18:44,330
What?

415
00:18:44,330 --> 00:18:45,830
Don't you guys want her to come!?

416
00:18:45,830 --> 00:18:47,110
It's not that!

417
00:18:47,110 --> 00:18:48,950
Vivi has to decide this on her own!

418
00:18:54,360 --> 00:18:56,280
Tomorrow at 12 noon...

419
00:18:56,600 --> 00:18:58,000
The eastern harbor...

420
00:18:58,270 --> 00:18:59,940
Carue can make it in four hours,

421
00:19:00,280 --> 00:19:02,540
So I'll have to leave here at 8 o'clock to make it in time.

422
00:19:03,440 --> 00:19:07,250
I've never considered becoming a pirate myself...

423
00:19:07,520 --> 00:19:09,680
The chance to choose between two different lives...

424
00:19:10,030 --> 00:19:13,920
...is something that will never be offered to me again.

425
00:19:15,290 --> 00:19:18,490
I've never thought being a princess was boring.

426
00:19:18,730 --> 00:19:20,400
And even with the rebellion over...

427
00:19:20,400 --> 00:19:22,430
...the country is still in a terrible state.

428
00:19:26,010 --> 00:19:27,880
If I went...

429
00:19:28,170 --> 00:19:30,110
You'd come too, right?

430
00:19:31,260 --> 00:19:34,250
Right, Carue?

431
00:19:35,610 --> 00:19:39,040
What do... you want to do?

432
00:19:40,890 --> 00:19:43,820
I WAS WAAAITING FOR YOU GUYS~!

433
00:19:43,820 --> 00:19:45,950
HOW LOVELY TO SEE YOU AGAIN~! 

434
00:19:46,260 --> 00:19:47,270
Alright, we made it.

435
00:19:47,270 --> 00:19:48,650
Unload our stuff!

436
00:19:48,650 --> 00:19:50,010
Thanks a lot, guys.

437
00:19:50,340 --> 00:19:52,490
This is farewell to you all as well!

438
00:19:52,490 --> 00:19:53,740
Take care going home!

439
00:19:54,010 --> 00:19:57,110
Send our regards to the King and the Chikuwa Ossan!

440
00:19:57,110 --> 00:19:58,750
Stay well!

441
00:19:58,750 --> 00:19:59,790
Some day...

442
00:20:00,090 --> 00:20:04,380
Some day, let us meet again!

443
00:20:06,930 --> 00:20:07,900
WHAT A BIG MINUTE!

444
00:20:07,900 --> 00:20:08,720
What is it now?

445
00:20:08,720 --> 00:20:10,390
What do you mean, "What is it now"!?

446
00:20:10,390 --> 00:20:14,200
What kind of attitude is that towards your friend!?

447
00:20:14,300 --> 00:20:15,590
What do you mean "friend"?

448
00:20:15,590 --> 00:20:16,830
You're our enemy!

449
00:20:16,830 --> 00:20:18,020
You tricked us.

450
00:20:18,020 --> 00:20:19,630
I did NOT trick you!

451
00:20:19,630 --> 00:20:21,770
I didn't know either!

452
00:20:21,770 --> 00:20:24,480
But, really... That's all in the past now...

453
00:20:24,480 --> 00:20:26,640
Baroque Works has crumbled.

454
00:20:26,640 --> 00:20:28,950
We're not enemies anymore.

455
00:20:28,950 --> 00:20:29,930
Shift over.

456
00:20:29,930 --> 00:20:30,670
Oh, sorry.

457
00:20:31,000 --> 00:20:34,840
If you're not our enemy, why the hell are you on our ship!?

458
00:20:35,340 --> 00:20:36,700
You silly, silly man!

459
00:20:36,700 --> 00:20:37,690
WHAT WAS THAT!?

460
00:20:37,890 --> 00:20:38,950
Look!

461
00:20:38,950 --> 00:20:40,670
If I wasn't on this ship right now,

462
00:20:40,670 --> 00:20:43,290
What do you think would have happened to it!?

463
00:20:43,290 --> 00:20:45,310
The Marine might have taken it.

464
00:20:45,310 --> 00:20:46,480
Not "MIGHT" have!

465
00:20:46,480 --> 00:20:47,800
It would have definitely been taken!

466
00:20:48,000 --> 00:20:50,970
Do you knooow what's happening to this island right now!?

467
00:20:50,970 --> 00:20:53,050
It's entirely blockaded by Marine ships!

468
00:20:53,050 --> 00:20:53,830
Blockaded!

469
00:20:53,830 --> 00:20:54,750
So then...

470
00:20:54,750 --> 00:20:58,070
You protected the Going Merry from the Marines!?

471
00:20:58,070 --> 00:20:58,590
Why!?

472
00:20:58,590 --> 00:20:59,560
What for!?

473
00:21:01,070 --> 00:21:03,130
Because we're friends!

474
00:21:09,910 --> 00:21:10,960
Is there any more to bring on?

475
00:21:10,960 --> 00:21:12,630
Nope! This is the last of it.

476
00:21:12,820 --> 00:21:14,330
So then, Mr. 2...

477
00:21:14,330 --> 00:21:18,640
With the Marine blockading the entire island, that would mean you couldn't escape either.

478
00:21:18,640 --> 00:21:20,970
And so you're using us to escape safely?

479
00:21:21,250 --> 00:21:22,320
BON-CHAN!

480
00:21:22,460 --> 00:21:23,400
Yes!

481
00:21:23,400 --> 00:21:25,910
Because we need each other!

482
00:21:25,910 --> 00:21:27,890
IN THE NAME OF SACRED FRIENDSHIP,

483
00:21:27,890 --> 00:21:30,790
LET US COMBINE OUR FORCES AND FIGHT TOGRTHER AS ONE!

484
00:21:37,270 --> 00:21:38,700
Thanks for helping us out!

485
00:21:38,700 --> 00:21:40,140
HOW LONG HAVE YOU BEEN THERE!?

486
00:21:40,760 --> 00:21:41,600
Hina-jou!

487
00:21:41,820 --> 00:21:42,850
Hina-jou!

488
00:21:43,410 --> 00:21:46,250
We've sighted them! It's the Straw Hat Pirates' vessel!

489
00:21:46,250 --> 00:21:48,190
They are upstream on the Sandora River!

490
00:21:49,930 --> 00:21:51,310
Prepare for battle.

